24/06/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The first government reshuffle is expected by the end of July, according to an article Monday (23 June) in <I>Fakti</I>, the most popular Albanian language daily. 
According to the report, the minor coalition partner Democratic Union for Integration (DUI) has already agreed to changes at the ministerial level, but has not named names. 
<I>Fakti</I> reports the reshuffle is the result of DUI's recent merger with the National Democratic Party. 
(Utrinski Vesnik - 24/06/03; MIA - 23/06/03)
